      "writtenOn": "2020-12-29T14:21:56Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027m sorry I didn\u0027t think of this when reading the design doc, but one lesson we learned in Gold was to version our APIs so that if we needed to migrate, we didn\u0027t have to worry about as much breakage. I think we would want to do the same thing here for a service that is designed to be used by different clients.\n\nI would suggest something as simple as /v1/ instead of /_/\n\nAlso handy on Gold was metrics showing per-API and per-Version usage\nhttps://github.com/google/skia-buildbot/blob/5c3f9d88dec9e4cc381c145fbf5fe185d0e0aad1/golden/cmd/skiacorrectness/skiacorrectness.go#L885",
